						               													<description>Fighting Formations is a fledgling series of games, which will focus on several battles of various individual formations during World War II. The first title in the series is &amp;quot;Grossdeutschland Infantry Division.&amp;quot; Future titles aren't yet set in stone but could be devoted to other famous divisions (Big Red One), Corps (Afrika Korps), regiments (442nd RCT), Commando troops, Ranger battalions, etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scale of the game is 75 meters per hex with turns representing about 5 minutes of real time. Units are squads, guns with their inherent crews, and individual vehicles. Platoons are also employed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has card Assets -- including such things as snipers, artillery, air support or demolitions -- but is not card-driven. It is also not the typical Igo-Yougo fare with a strict sequence of play. Instead, the base game engine is an impulse-type back and forth mechanic whereby the various Orders carry with them a certain cost in Initiative, with the person having the most Initiative at any given time being able to take the next action on the map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This first game has the following components:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4 22&amp;quot; x 34&amp;quot; back-printed mapsheets&amp;#10;5 countersheets&amp;#10;55 cards&amp;#10;24-page series rulebook&amp;#10;48-page playbook&amp;#10;an 8.5&amp;quot; x 22&amp;quot; track display&amp;#10;several cardstock player aids&amp;#10;dice: 2d6, 2d8, 2d10, 2d12 &amp;amp; 2d20&amp;#10;10 wooden cubes&amp;#10;1 wooden pawn&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Fighting Formations FAQ&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
